<section id="about">
  <div class="container">
    <h2 class="section-title">About</h2>
    <div class="about-content">
      <p>
        I'm a PhD candidate in Physics at <strong>Northeastern University</strong>, affiliated with the
        <a href="https://www.mighte.org/" target="_blank">MIGHTE Lab</a>
        (PI: Mauricio Santillana). My research sits at the intersection of machine learning
        and data science with epidemiology and health care.
      </p>
      <p>
        I build ML systems and data-driven solutions that have real-world impact: an early warning
        system for respiratory disease across all 50 US states, built in collaboration with the
        <strong>CDC</strong>; a deep learning pipeline to detect diabetic retinopathy from
        retinal images; and Bayesian/MCMC frameworks for uncertainty quantification in
        outbreak forecasting models. My day-to-day involves working with large-scale,
        messy datasets, from data ingestion and analysis through modeling, experimentation,
        and communicating results to both technical and non-technical stakeholders.
      </p>
      <p>
        I'm actively seeking roles in <strong>data science</strong>, <strong>machine learning</strong>,
        and <strong>applied science</strong> where I can bring research-level rigor and
        end-to-end pipeline experience to production systems.
      </p>

